many students have questions about when they will receive their financial aid disbursement. the best way to determine when your disbursement will occur is to regularly review and monitor your account on mysjsu . financial aid funds are downloaded to sjsu on wednesdays. by the end of the day, an entry will appear on your account with the amount(s) awarded. there may be more than one line item depending on how many types of awards you receive. after all of your outstanding fees are paid, then any remaining credit balance will be disbursed to you via electronic refund (direct deposit) or paper check. to sign up, see how to enroll in direct deposit (erefunds) [pdf] . the refund will appear on your account (under ) as and will display the amount of the erefund that is being sent to you electronically or the amount of the paper check that is being mailed to the address you have on file with sjsu. please note that it may take up to three business days for the direct deposit (erefund) to be deposited in your designated bank account, or up to 5-10 days for you to receive the paper check via mail. phone: 408-924-1601 monday - friday 9:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m. live chat: mondays and wednesdays 1:00 - 3:00 p.m. tuesdays and thursdays 7:30 - 10:00 a.m. fridays 9:00 am - 12:00 noon email: bursar@sjsu.edu response time is one to three business days. deposits can be placed in the depository box at the student services center and is located to the right of the main doors.  begin comm100 live chat code student services center 9th and san fernando st san josé, ca 95192-0138 to talk to a bursar’s office staff member in person, online you can choose to be notified by text as your turn approaches. monday - thursday 8:15 a.m. - 4:30 p.m. friday 9:00 a.m. - 4:30 p.m. 